Installation Instructions
*************************


The scripts and the module use the Python-setuptools packaging systems.
Just be sure than Python is installed on your computer.
If you do not have already the setuptools package installed, the setup.py script will automaticaly
use the ez_setup.py bootstrap to install savebases. You may install first setuptools with :
| python ez_setup.py


----
To install savebases as root :

1) create the directories where the saves will be keeps if they did not exists :
| su mkdir /home/base/sauve_jours
| su mkdir /home/base/sauve_semaines
| su mkdir /home/base/sauve_mois

2) Unpack the distribution somewhere like /usr/local/src
| tar zxvf savebases-x.x.tar.gz

3) Enter into this directory and just type :
| python setup.py install

4) Create symbolic links to automate the scripts with cron :
| ln -s /usr/local/bin/savedb_day.sh /etc/cron.daily/savedb_day.sh
| ln -s /usr/local/bin/savedb_week.sh /etc/cron.weekly/savedb_week.sh
| ln -s /usr/local/bin/savedb_month.sh /etc/cron.monthly/savedb_month.sh

5) Change the configuration file if necessary :
/etc/savebases.conf


Note : The setup.py script will :
- Create a module for the scripts under /sur/local/lib/python2.x/site-packages/savebases.py
(or under /usr/local/lib64 if you have a x64 machine)
- Create scripts under /usr/local/bin :
/usr/local/bin/sauvedb_day.sh
/usr/local/bin/sauvedb_week.sh
/usr/local/bin/sauvedb_month.sh

